#1 Metastatic colorectal cancer to the lungs
#2 Possible abscess in the pelvis
The lung nodules are small and have not changed.  At this point, I would not recommend consideration for any operation to the lung nodules, and I would not recommend chemotherapy.  Observation for another two-to-three months is in order to see what happens to her lungs before any decisions are made on whether attempt at surgical resection of those nodules is reasonable and possible or advisable.
Regarding the fluid collection in the pelvic area, I would leave this up to Dr. Batchelor who is seeing the patient later today and whether intervention is needed.  The patient's difficulty to sit may be related to this, but things have not been getting worse, and she does not seem to be having clinically an active infection, although this is not my area of expertise.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

